13
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:36,020
-About the...
-How did you know Xia Chu?

14
00:02:45,020 --> 00:02:46,670
We started as Internet friends.

15
00:02:47,970 --> 00:02:48,810
I found an article

16
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:50,810
she wrote on the Internet

17
00:02:51,670 --> 00:02:52,960
about her first love.

18
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:54,560
At that time,

19
00:02:54,770 --> 00:02:56,040
I was about to graduate from university.

20
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:58,090
I couldn't find a job yet.

21
00:02:58,810 --> 00:03:00,590
Quota for postgraduate studies
had all been filled up.

22
00:03:00,850 --> 00:03:01,810
My boyfriend wanted to break up with me.

23
00:03:01,910 --> 00:03:03,290
I was extremely depressed.

24
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,670
But after reading her article,

25
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:06,860
I was inspired.

26
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,580
I replied to her article.

27
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:11,840
Then, we started texting
each other on WeChat.

28
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:15,080
Later on, we arranged a meet-up.

29
00:03:15,350 --> 00:03:16,690
It's kind of weird.

30
00:03:17,270 --> 00:03:19,010
Although our age gap

31
00:03:19,670 --> 00:03:21,380
is quite big

32
00:03:21,830 --> 00:03:23,380
and our personalities are so different,

33
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,490
but somehow we had

34
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:26,470
endless topics to talk about
every time we meet.

35
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,650
Maybe it's because

36
00:03:31,750 --> 00:03:33,370
we are both brilliant individuals

37
00:03:33,510 --> 00:03:37,040
and role models of outstanding
contemporary young women?

38
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:39,540
Hence we empathize and admire each other.

39
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,810
Did she ever mention to you about...

40
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,620
You?

41
00:03:45,010 --> 00:03:46,070
Yes.

42
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:47,310
Me.

43
00:03:47,890 --> 00:03:48,610
Of course she did.

44
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:49,660
She told me a lot

45
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:51,370
about your past with her.

46
00:03:51,550 --> 00:03:52,430
What happened after that?

47
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:55,590
Was she in a new relationship?

48
00:03:55,670 --> 00:03:56,930
She had a relationship
during her university years

49
00:03:57,650 --> 00:03:58,830
but it ended very soon.

50
00:03:59,490 --> 00:04:00,550
She was too busy.

51
00:04:05,530 --> 00:04:06,630
Too busy?

52
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:09,210
Perhaps it was because she was too busy.

53
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,490
Perhaps it was because of other reasons.

54
00:04:12,370 --> 00:04:13,470
Perhaps it was because of you.

55
00:04:17,450 --> 00:04:18,640
What do you want to know?

56
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:25,130
<i>Long Yi</i>

57
00:04:25,659 --> 00:04:26,640
Please excuse me.

58
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:34,480
<i>His name is Liang Mu Ze.</i>

59
00:04:34,670 --> 00:04:35,800
<i>He's from the Special Forces.</i>

60
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:37,850
<i>Now an army major.</i>

61
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:39,620
<i>Xia Chu is close to him.</i>

62
00:04:40,130 --> 00:04:42,820
<i>They're living in together now.</i>

63
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:44,300
I got it.

64
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:54,150
It's fine.

65
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,370
You should get going if you're busy.
Don't worry about me.

66
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:01,200
It's him.

67
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:09,840
It's really him.

68
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:11,810
Are you okay?

69
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:28,270
<i>Outpatient Department</i>

70
00:05:25,830 --> 00:05:27,060
Please clear the front.

71
00:05:27,230 --> 00:05:28,530
Make way, please.

72
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,380
Please make way.

73
00:05:34,930 --> 00:05:36,470
I'm sorry. You have to wait outside.

74
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,120
<i>Military and Police Take Down Drug Den</i>

75
00:06:12,350 --> 00:06:14,600
Cheers to our final night together.

76
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:22,360
Is everyone ready?

77
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:24,500
This is the final test
of this military training program,

78
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:26,250
namely the endurance test.

79
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:29,240
It's the ultimate test of your willpower.

80
00:06:29,570 --> 00:06:32,260
As soon as someone touches the tear gas,

81
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:33,920
I'll start the timer.

82
00:06:34,690 --> 00:06:37,440
The test ends when each individual
leaves this room

83
00:06:37,530 --> 00:06:39,190
and marks will be added
into your final scores.

84
00:06:40,590 --> 00:06:41,600
In other words,

85
00:06:41,690 --> 00:06:43,190
as long as you stay
in this room long enough,

86
00:06:43,380 --> 00:06:45,230
you can still catch up with the scores
although you were behind?

87
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,230
That's right.

88
00:06:46,350 --> 00:06:47,830
Good luck to everyone.

89
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,730
It's going to be a tough one today.

90
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:51,380
Liang Mu Ze.

91
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:52,780
You'll put the tear gas

92
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:54,420
-into the pot.
-Okay.

93
00:06:56,359 --> 00:06:57,540
Let's make a deal first.

94
00:06:57,910 --> 00:06:59,180
Whoever leaves this room first

95
00:06:59,270 --> 00:07:00,140
will buy everyone a meal.

96
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:02,010
-Sure.
-No problem.

97
00:07:03,570 --> 00:07:04,640
Liang Mu Ze.

98
00:07:05,109 --> 00:07:06,920
How could you start
without telling us first?

99
00:07:08,110 --> 00:07:09,450
I'm going all out.

100
00:07:14,230 --> 00:07:15,260
I really want to know

101
00:07:15,350 --> 00:07:16,260
if you were ever defeated before

102
00:07:16,350 --> 00:07:18,210
all these years in the force.

103
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,240
Of course he was.

104
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:22,730
I'll take him down today.

105
00:07:23,460 --> 00:07:24,510
I want to know

106
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:26,960
who that legend is.

107
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:28,570
I must meet him.

108
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:32,090
You can't meet him anymore.

109
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,360
He died in service.

110
00:07:37,590 --> 00:07:38,330
If it wasn't for him,

111
00:07:38,420 --> 00:07:39,590
I wouldn't be sitting here alive today.

112
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:37,590
This is wrong.

113
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:39,700
What did you say?

114
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:41,410
You should walk ahead of me.

115
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,820
Is there a difference?

116
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:49,050
It'll be the right direction
when you walk ahead of me.

117
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,480
Following you keeps me steady.

118
00:09:53,490 --> 00:09:55,870
It has been eight years, Mu Ze.

119
00:09:56,970 --> 00:09:58,980
You don't have to walk in my footsteps.

120
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:00,200
I need to.

121
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:03,320
To others,

122
00:10:04,060 --> 00:10:06,160
many things may change in eight years.

123
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:08,420
But to me,

124
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:12,080
you'll always be my captain.

125
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,520
The patient is experiencing
ventricular tachycardia.

126
00:11:22,630 --> 00:11:23,300
Get the defibrillator.

127
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:24,890
IV infusion, 100 mg of lidocaine.

128
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:34,720
Heart rate is back to normal.

129
00:12:35,340 --> 00:12:38,730
Why did you drink so much today?

130
00:12:38,890 --> 00:12:41,100
Don't you have to
return to the force tomorrow?

131
00:12:42,810 --> 00:12:44,750
Stop drinking. It's bad for your stomach.

132
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:48,770
Tomorrow is an off day.

133
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:52,440
You cried?

134
00:12:53,370 --> 00:12:54,470
Tear gas.

135
00:13:00,790 --> 00:13:01,800
My head hurts.

136
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:04,610
I'll make you honey drink to sober up.

137
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:23,060
Sit down and talk with me.

138
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,370
Today is the anniversary of

139
00:13:39,350 --> 00:13:40,250
Luo Liang's death.

140
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,020
Luo Liang?

141
00:13:42,140 --> 00:13:43,070
Yes.

142
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:45,760
Xiao Jun's father.

143
00:13:47,620 --> 00:13:48,930
You were right.

144
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,230
Eight years have passed.

145
00:13:53,790 --> 00:13:55,280
But I still think he is here.

146
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:57,850
He is still by my side

147
00:13:58,270 --> 00:13:59,610
and in my life.

148
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:02,790
Sometimes when I'm in my dreams

149
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:05,970
or when I had too much to drink,

150
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:08,120
I'll want to talk to him.

151
00:14:13,570 --> 00:14:15,380
I can't believe and accept the fact that

152
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:18,260
he has totally disappeared

153
00:14:18,350 --> 00:14:19,730
from my life.

154
00:14:19,950 --> 00:14:20,970
I can't accept it.

155
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:34,010
<i>Luo Liang and I</i>

156
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:36,530
<i>majored in Special Forces
Military Training.</i>

157
00:14:37,590 --> 00:14:40,050
<i>We joined the Special Forces Brigade
after we graduated.</i>

158
00:14:40,510 --> 00:14:43,090
<i>Like our Brigade Captain Dong Zhi Gang
always said,</i>

159
00:14:43,190 --> 00:14:44,710
<i>"When two similar sharp edges</i>

160
00:14:44,790 --> 00:14:46,370
<i>with the same shine meet,</i>

161
00:14:47,350 --> 00:14:48,530
<i>sparks will fly</i>

162
00:14:48,670 --> 00:14:50,890
<i>when they collide."</i>

163
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:52,850
<i>We graduated the same year,</i>

164
00:14:53,230 --> 00:14:54,810
<i>served under the same force,</i>

165
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:56,850
<i>and became platoon sergeants.</i>

166
00:14:57,620 --> 00:14:58,960
<i>Everything was a competition between us.</i>

167
00:15:00,050 --> 00:15:02,270
<i>We competed in our trainings</i>

168
00:15:02,810 --> 00:15:04,630
<i>and shooting skills.</i>

169
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,700
Start!

170
00:15:16,470 --> 00:15:19,860
-Beat him!
-You can do it!

171
00:15:19,950 --> 00:15:21,470
<i>Even in the activity room
during break time,</i>

172
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:23,300
<i>we competed in</i>

173
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:25,610
<i>arm wrestling.</i>

174
00:15:26,430 --> 00:15:28,620
You can do it!

175
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:31,210
You can do it!

176
00:15:31,470 --> 00:15:32,930
<i>Those were the days in the force.</i>

177
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:34,890
<i>Everything was a competition.</i>

178
00:15:35,530 --> 00:15:36,760
<i>There must be a winner
and loser in everything.</i>

179
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:39,050
<i>Everyone gave his very best.</i>

180
00:15:40,130 --> 00:15:42,830
Being passionate in everything
was the law of survival in the force.

181
00:15:44,470 --> 00:15:45,970
It was also a special way of expressing

182
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:48,600
the friendship between Luo Liang and me.

183
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:52,050
At that time, comrades in the force

184
00:15:52,140 --> 00:15:53,290
would call us

185
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:57,920
military elites who are equally matched.

186
00:15:58,870 --> 00:16:00,010
When we were

187
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:02,850
at the peak of our competition,

188
00:16:05,350 --> 00:16:06,590
the force wanted to form

189
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:08,250
a younger special operations force.

190
00:16:08,870 --> 00:16:10,620
All the young officers
in the special force

191
00:16:10,710 --> 00:16:12,130
signed up for the position

192
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:13,770
of captain.

193
00:16:14,950 --> 00:16:16,810
<i>After many rounds of tests,</i>

194
00:16:16,970 --> 00:16:18,470
<i>it was down to Luo Liang</i>

195
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:20,170
<i>and me.</i>

196
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,580
<i>How did it go?</i>

197
00:16:21,670 --> 00:16:22,890
<i>I lost to him.</i>

198
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,630
Why didn't you attend

199
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,780
our first training this afternoon?

200
00:16:28,370 --> 00:16:29,830
I was tired so I didn't want to go.

201
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:38,380
No matter how tired you are,
you're still the lieutenant.

202
00:16:38,790 --> 00:16:40,930
Bond with the team and train warriors.

203
00:16:41,150 --> 00:16:43,220
The entire brigade is watching us now.

204
00:16:43,380 --> 00:16:46,010
No matter how tired you are,
you have to endure it.

205
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:48,150
In that case, I'll withdraw
from Team Thunder tomorrow.

206
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,130
I don't care who becomes the lieutenant.

207
00:16:53,230 --> 00:16:54,640
Now that I'm Team Thunder's captain,

208
00:16:55,510 --> 00:16:56,730
you are dissatisfied?

209
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:00,000
Answer me.

210
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:02,310
Yes, I am.

211
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:04,210
Didn't you see the test results?

212
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:06,200
What makes you captain? Tell me.

213
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:07,190
What makes you?

214
00:17:09,490 --> 00:17:11,230
The way you're behaving now
says that I'm more worthy.

215
00:17:12,710 --> 00:17:14,690
You're not fit to be
captain of Team Thunder.

216
00:17:15,330 --> 00:17:17,059
You don't even have the basic qualities

217
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,250
of a soldier.

218
00:17:18,350 --> 00:17:19,450
Shut up.

219
00:17:19,910 --> 00:17:21,480
I don't need a lecture from you.
Get lost.

220
00:17:23,390 --> 00:17:24,559
As a soldier,

221
00:17:25,590 --> 00:17:27,019
you rise from where you fall

222
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:28,640
on the battlefield.

223
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,610
Taking things personal like this,

224
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:33,920
giving others your attitude
and giving up on yourself

225
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:35,410
make you a coward.

226
00:17:57,830 --> 00:17:58,850
Do you feel better now?

227
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:00,450
Get up. Let's continue.

228
00:18:03,470 --> 00:18:04,350
No.

229
00:18:05,350 --> 00:18:06,970
You've already wasted a lot of energy
punching the sand bag today.

230
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:09,970
If we continue to fight,
I won't win fairly.

231
00:18:10,670 --> 00:18:11,810
How are you so sure that you'll win?

232
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:14,790
We'll become rivals for a lifetime,
won't we?

233
00:18:16,620 --> 00:18:17,570
There's still a long way to go.

234
00:18:18,110 --> 00:18:19,970
We don't have to do this now.

235
00:18:22,260 --> 00:18:23,600
The Brigade Captain told me that

236
00:18:24,420 --> 00:18:25,930
you're a good sword.

237
00:18:26,590 --> 00:18:28,010
But you still need to be sharpened.

238
00:18:28,790 --> 00:18:30,770
It might do you good

239
00:18:31,790 --> 00:18:33,330
that you're not captain.

240
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:36,090
Tomorrow morning at nine o'clock,

241
00:18:36,270 --> 00:18:38,100
gather for indoor close-quarters combat.

242
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:40,040
I'm busy. You can proceed without me.

243
00:18:40,430 --> 00:18:41,620
Don't you dare.

244
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:50,150
Sir.

245
00:18:50,390 --> 00:18:51,630
Lieutenant of Team Thunder,

246
00:18:51,710 --> 00:18:53,770
code name Whale, requests to return.

247
00:18:54,220 --> 00:18:55,120
Fall in.

248
00:18:59,170 --> 00:19:00,390
From today onwards,

249
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:02,570
not a single soldier here

250
00:19:03,260 --> 00:19:04,600
will be left behind.

251
00:19:05,110 --> 00:19:06,170
Do you hear me?

252
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:09,200
Only death will keep us apart.

253
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:16,460
Xiao Jun's mother said

254
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:19,740
you went on a mission together.

255
00:19:20,970 --> 00:19:22,070
Yes.

256
00:19:24,150 --> 00:19:25,490
We went on a mission together

257
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:31,630
but he didn't return.

258
00:19:35,630 --> 00:19:36,890
He was the only one who didn't return.

259
00:19:55,030 --> 00:19:56,010
As usual,

260
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:58,850
write your will and
the receiver's address.

261
00:19:59,070 --> 00:20:00,490
Submit it before you disembark.

262
00:20:14,310 --> 00:20:16,120
Captain, aren't you going to write one?

263
00:20:16,270 --> 00:20:19,130
Meng Zhen doesn't want to do it. She said
she'll be waiting for me to go home.

264
00:20:20,430 --> 00:20:21,490
Is she going to deliver soon?

265
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:23,490
One more month to go.

266
00:20:25,260 --> 00:20:27,210
If I don't make it back,

267
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:28,780
you guys have to look after

268
00:20:28,870 --> 00:20:30,610
the baby and her for me.

269
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:31,550
Don't worry.

270
00:20:31,630 --> 00:20:33,650
Your son is also my son.

271
00:20:34,790 --> 00:20:36,040
In your dreams!

272
00:20:36,450 --> 00:20:38,150
Your parents are also my parents.

273
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:40,250
Your pet is also my pet.

274
00:20:41,750 --> 00:20:43,250
Do you remember that poem we recited

275
